#
# The str.format() method in Python inserts dynamic values and variables into
# specific placeholders within a template string.
# It works by searching a string for curly braces {}, which act as placeholders,
# and replacing them with the arguments passed directly into the method.

# To control how data looks activate these features by placing a column : inside
# curly braces followed by a format specifier.

#Decimal precision -
